<P align=center><B><FONT size=5>Alternate Site Games, 1901-2000</FONT></B></P>
<P>This list shows games played <font color="#FF0000">in 1901-2000</font> by major league clubs in a ballpark and/or city 
that is not home to either team. There have been many reasons that these games 
have been moved through the years such as Sunday Blue Laws, park capacity and 
fires. Most of these games are between teams in the same league but a few of the 
more recent contests are interleague.</P>
<P>This data was compiled by David Vincent and others from many different sources. If you 
find an error or have data to add, please contact the webmaster.
</P>
<P>To see the 19th century games, <a href="neutral19.htm">click here</a>.<br>
To see the 21st century games, <a href="neutral.htm">click here</a>.</P>

Additions, changes (for older years):<BR>
11/22/2020: Split in three lists by century
8/23/2019: Corrected visiting team on 5/17/1911<br>
12/31/2011: Reason for 8/1/1914, 8/8/1914 changed from (6) to (12)<br>
4/17/2010: Added games in Detroit in 1901-02<br>
11/6/2009: Added 1916 World Series games in Boston<br>
10/30/2009: Added games in Boston on 10/3/1916, 4/19/1930, 7/4/1930, 4/19/1932<br>
10/18/2007: Added many games and split into two lists</p>

